Butternut Squash and Red Pepper Soup
  --Cook's Country

4 oz pancetta, cut into 1/2" pieces
2 lb butternut squash, peeled, seeded, and cut into 1" pieces (6 c)
1 red bell pepper, stemmed, seeded, and chopped
1 onion, chopped fine
3 garlic cloves, minced
1 tsp dried thyme
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp pepper
4 c chicken broth
1 tsp sherry vinegar
2 tbsp chopped fresh chives

Cook pancetta in dutch oven over medium heat until browned and crispy, ~ 7 min. Using slotted spoon, transfer pancetta to paper towel lines plate. Add squash, bell pepper, onion, garlic, thyme, salt, and pepper to fat left in pot and cook over medium high heat until onion is softened, ~5 min, stirring ocasionally. Stir in broth and bring to boil, scraping up any fond. Cook, covered, until squash is tender, ~15 min. Remove pot from heat. Working with 2 c at a time, process soup in blender until smooth, ~1 min. Transfer pureed soup to saucepan. Stir in vinegar. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve, sprinkle individual portions with chives and pancetta.


Notes: use 4 oz hunk of pancetta, not presliced variety
